                      <L n="variations">
                        <T>0xA117A82<!--A group of tigers is called a Streak or an Ambush! While tigers are typically solitary animals, they will sometimes form groups to care for cubs or to hunt for food. The last thing anyone would want is to be ambushed by an Ambush!--></T>
                        <T>0x982F3678<!--Like most members of their genus, tigers have various forms of communication. Because of their flexible larynx and hyoid apparatus, they can't purr like your typical house cat, but it does give them what they need to let out a ferocious roar! They are also known to growl and chuff. Scent marking and tree scratching are used as a silent way to let other tigers know this area is claimed.\n\nWhile cute, tigers are wild animals and should not be approached. A snuggle today could mean trouble tomorrow!--></T>
                        <T>0xE0CB1B8A<!--Tigers live in tropical rainforests, deciduous, evergreen, subtropical and tropical dry broadleaf forests, including the areas surrounding Tomarang. They are incredible swimmers, able to cross large rivers with ease. Tigers are also nocturnal creatures, which is why Sims may just catch a glimpse of them in the brush after sunset. --></T>
                      </L>
